00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:14,280
Oh, but objectively speaking, that's just no fun.

274
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:17,080
It's a violation of human rights.

275
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:22,080
Let me be a part of the special exhibition.

276
00:18:22,080 --> 00:18:24,760
Just imagine how hard I'll work, since Si-an's involved in this.

277
00:18:24,760 --> 00:18:26,320
No, because I'm worried you'll work too hard.

278
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:28,040
But Director??

279
00:18:28,040 --> 00:18:30,880
Um, how about letting her try?

280
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:37,160
For example, merchandise planning?

281
00:18:37,160 --> 00:18:38,640
Merchandise planning?

282
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:41,760
In other words, like goods.

283
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:43,360
But related to the exhibition.

284
00:18:43,360 --> 00:18:47,760
But museum merchandise is just pencils and postcards, isn't it?

285
00:18:47,760 --> 00:18:49,680
Sounds boring.

286
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:52,280
Forget that. How about our Si-an's special exh??

287
00:18:52,280 --> 00:18:54,920
Oh, we need merchandise for the special exhibition, too.

288
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:57,000
I'll plan them! The goods.

289
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:00,000
How am I supposed to entrust you with this

290
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:03,200
when you've shown me neither your responsibility nor diligence?

291
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:06,160
I'll show you from now on.

292
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:09,920
Sometimes, positions maketh man.

293
00:19:17,840 --> 00:19:21,080
On one condition: All internal documents

294
00:19:21,080 --> 00:19:23,080
and meeting minutes must be kept confidential.

295
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:24,080
Yes, sir.

296
00:19:32,840 --> 00:19:35,440
Who was in charge of product planning until now?

297
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:37,680
Curator Sung and I were.

298
00:19:37,680 --> 00:19:39,120
So that's why they were so blah.

299
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:50,000
- Curator Sung. - Yes?

300
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,760
Are you free this afternoon?

301
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:53,240
Ah, yes.

302
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:55,280
Then come somewhere with me.

303
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:56,240
To where?

304
00:19:56,240 --> 00:19:57,480
You'll know when we get there.

305
00:19:58,560 --> 00:20:01,080
I'll see you at the parking lot in 30 minutes.

306
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:05,360
Oh!

307
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,760
Make sure you look good.

308
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:18,040
A meeting with Mr. Cha Si-an?

309
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:21,360
I couldn't meet with him yesterday because something came up.

310
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,040
Then why did you tell me to make sure I look good?

311
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,720
The last time Mr. Cha Si-an was here,

312
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:30,520
everyone seemed to be self-conscious.

313
00:21:30,520 --> 00:21:33,200
Cu. Yoo and Hyo-jin as well.

314
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:34,520
Absolutely everyone.

315
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:36,360
I was mistaken again??

316
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:39,920
Again?

317
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:41,120
Again what?

318
00:21:41,120 --> 00:21:43,040
Oh, it's nothing.

319
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:55,960
One!

320
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:58,120
All rise!

321
00:21:59,280 --> 00:22:00,320
Come on, up!

322
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:01,920
Two!

323
00:22:13,360 --> 00:22:17,080
- Hello! - Hello!

324
00:22:17,080 --> 00:22:19,640
Yes, hello.

325
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:21,600
Gosh, you're all so adorable.

326
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:24,160
Alright, face the front!

327
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:26,080
Who's distracted in the middle of training, huh?

328
00:22:26,080 --> 00:22:27,000
One!

329
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:30,080
Now, get up!

330
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:31,960
Two!

331
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:36,280
You need to hurry up! Come on, up!

332
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:38,360
Hey, hey, hey!

333
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:42,520
Stop it, you'll catch a cold!

334
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:55,960
Come on, up!

335
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:58,040
Two!

336
00:23:01,040 --> 00:23:02,600
Let's see who's the first one to get up.

337
00:23:02,600 --> 00:23:04,000
Come on, up!

338
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,080
One!

339
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:08,520
Two!

340
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:12,320
You need to get up faster.

341
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:16,520
Two!

342
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:23,040
Mom.

343
00:23:23,040 --> 00:23:23,880
Ah.

344
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:33,440
When did that get on my face?

345
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:44,120
It's not like that.

346
00:23:44,120 --> 00:23:45,000
Here.

347
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:47,640
Eat up.

348
00:23:47,640 --> 00:23:49,200
Wow, looks delicious!

349
00:23:49,200 --> 00:23:52,120
Son, are you mad at me?

350
00:23:52,120 --> 00:23:53,960
Mad at you?

351
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:56,080
What's there to get mad about between a mother and son?

352
00:23:56,080 --> 00:23:58,320
Then why won't you come home these days?

353
00:23:58,320 --> 00:24:01,000
You've grown so haggard because you haven't been eating properly.

354
00:24:04,040 --> 00:24:07,000
If I ate like this every day, I'd be twice the size I am now.

355
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:09,360
Tsk, you say that, but??

356
00:24:09,360 --> 00:24:11,200
Mom.

357
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:13,160
Let's have some meat tonight. I'll buy.

358
00:24:15,040 --> 00:24:16,360
Tell Duk-mi to come home, too.

359
00:24:16,360 --> 00:24:19,040
Tell her to have dinner at home, no matter what.

360
00:24:19,040 --> 00:24:20,080
Alright?

361
00:24:22,040 --> 00:24:23,360
Mmm, yum!

362
00:24:26,320 --> 00:24:28,720
Your visual director just disappeared, without a word?

363
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:30,320
We thought we could trust him,

364
00:24:30,320 --> 00:24:32,720
but I guess you can't know everything about a person.

365
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:38,160
Which is why, uh??About the exhibition??

366
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:41,600
You're not trying to say that you can no longer participate, right?

367
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:43,040
I'm sorry, Director.

368
00:24:43,040 --> 00:24:46,400
But I can't afford to postpone my new single for this,

369
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:49,080
nor can I ask you to postpone this exhibition just for me??

370
00:24:49,080 --> 00:24:50,040
What about other directors?

371
00:24:50,040 --> 00:24:51,800
I am still looking,

372
00:24:53,080 --> 00:24:54,760
but I haven't exactly found anyone??

373
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:00,120
By any chance,

374
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:03,200
have you heard of Choi Da-in?

375
00:25:03,200 --> 00:25:05,120
Of course I have.

376
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:07,600
I've contacted her many times for a chance to work with her.

377
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:09,120
If Ms. Choi says

378
00:25:09,120 --> 00:25:12,120
she'll take over as your visual director,

379
00:25:12,120 --> 00:25:14,480
would you be able to carry on as planned?

380
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:16,760
Of course.

381
00:25:16,760 --> 00:25:19,320
Do you know Ms. Choi Da-in?

382
00:25:19,840 --> 00:25:21,120
I know her very well.

383
00:25:23,520 --> 00:25:24,720
I'm Choi Da-in.

384
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:29,640
I missed you, Ryan.

385
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:32,520
It'd be really nice if she agreed.

386
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:35,280
Please put in a good word for me.

387
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:37,520
I'll contact her, then.

388
00:25:37,520 --> 00:25:38,520
Please.

389
00:25:44,040 --> 00:25:46,360
There won't be a problem with our schedule, then.

390
00:25:46,360 --> 00:25:48,640
Ms. Choi Da-in??It's her, isn't it?

391
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:50,480
The one who came to see you at the museum?

392
00:25:50,480 --> 00:25:52,360
You've met her, right?

393
00:25:52,360 --> 00:25:54,280
She's a talented artist.

394
00:25:54,280 --> 00:25:57,840
Her participation will help with our publicity, too.

395
00:25:57,840 --> 00:26:00,400
But will she do it? The timeline's so tight.

396
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:02,800
She will.

397
00:26:02,800 --> 00:26:04,480
You sound very sure.

398
00:26:05,360 --> 00:26:08,440
It's the first time I'm asking her for a favor in 10 years,

399
00:26:08,440 --> 00:26:10,160
so she'll say yes. If she has a conscience.

400
00:26:11,160 --> 00:26:12,640
10 years??

401
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:16,760
Besides, I had a favor to ask her anyway for the exhibition.

402
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:18,600
She's the owner of the late photographer

403
00:26:18,600 --> 00:26:20,080
Yoon Tae-hwa's last work.

404
00:26:20,080 --> 00:26:22,840
If she is, then "Many People" is??

405
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:24,400
Da-in.

406
00:26:25,240 --> 00:26:27,000
That was the pseudonym I came up with for her

407
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:28,520
when we first met,

408
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:30,480
but who knew she'd be using it until now??

409
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:37,200
That's right. Curator Sung.

410
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:38,000
Yes?

411
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:39,320
Are you free today?

412
00:26:39,320 --> 00:26:42,240
Oh, I thought we'd finish early, so I told Mom I'd have dinner

413
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:44,120
- at home. But I can always cancel. - That's alright.

414
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:46,160
It's nothing urgent. Get in.

415
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:03,440
This is Ryan Gold, who made a reservation for 7 p.m.

416
00:27:03,440 --> 00:27:06,880
I'm sorry, but I'll have to cancel that reservation.

417
00:27:07,680 --> 00:27:08,680
Yes.

418
00:27:23,040 --> 00:27:24,360
Have a safe drive.

419
00:27:25,400 --> 00:27:28,560
That's right. What should I do about that interview with Moment?

420
00:27:28,560 --> 00:27:31,000
You find a time for me, Curator Sung.

421
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:31,920
Alright.

422
00:27:31,920 --> 00:27:35,080
Oh, and I'm going straight to Ms. Choi's studio tomorrow.

423
00:27:36,160 --> 00:27:37,280
Do you want to come with me?

424
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:40,120
Yes.

425
00:27:40,120 --> 00:27:41,760
I'll see you tomorrow, then.

426
00:28:16,920 --> 00:28:18,040
Director Nam Eun-ki?

427
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:22,200
How long will you keep up that fake relationship thing?

428
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:24,480
That Cheum-patch or whatever is gone now,

429
00:28:24,480 --> 00:28:26,200
so why not just end it here?

430
00:28:27,520 --> 00:28:30,120
That's for us to decide, and not for you to??

431
00:28:30,120 --> 00:28:31,120
"Us"?

432
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:35,760
Are you interested in Duk-mi, by any chance?

433
00:28:39,080 --> 00:28:41,720
That's also none of your business??

434
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:43,880
It is my business.

435
00:28:43,880 --> 00:28:46,000
Don't change the subject, and answer me.

436
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:47,680
Are you interested in Duk-mi?

437
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:50,080
I am.

438
00:28:52,040 --> 00:28:54,960
I think she's a good person. Ms. Sung Duk-mi, I mean.

439
00:28:56,560 --> 00:28:58,800
Is that purely out of human interest?

440
00:28:59,720 --> 00:29:02,320
Like how you helped her out

441
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:03,880
when you thought she was dating Sun-joo?

442
00:29:07,360 --> 00:29:08,760
If not, then what?

443
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:12,520
I don't see why I should answer that question.

444
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:13,640
Just put an end to it,

445
00:29:15,080 --> 00:29:17,440
instead of stirring her up for nothing.

446
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:22,800
Was she stirred up? Sung Duk-mi?

447
00:29:26,880 --> 00:29:28,920
I repeat,

448
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:31,320
this is for Curator Sung and me to decide.

449
00:29:31,320 --> 00:29:34,080
I don't need your advice, Director Nam.

450
00:29:37,040 --> 00:29:39,000
How much do you know about Duk-mi, anyway?

451
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:42,960
You see, there isn't anything I don't know about her.

452
00:29:44,280 --> 00:29:46,360
I know enough.

453
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:48,440
More than you think I know.

454
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:52,920
There's no way Duk-mi would tell you about herself.

455
00:29:56,080 --> 00:29:59,040
See, she tells me everything.

456
00:29:59,040 --> 00:30:00,600
Without hiding anything.

457
00:30:01,720 --> 00:30:04,120
But do you think she'll do the same with you?

458
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:24,160
Done.

459
00:30:29,120 --> 00:30:30,840
- Watch it. - Watch it!

460
00:30:30,840 --> 00:30:32,640
Stop that, before I punch your teeth out.

461
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:34,160
My teeth are too precious, though.

462
00:30:34,160 --> 00:30:35,600
- Hey! - What?

463
00:30:35,600 --> 00:30:36,920
You??

464
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:45,440
- Sung Duk-mi. - Yeah?

465
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:49,760
Director Ry is doing well, right?

466
00:30:49,760 --> 00:30:51,480
Mom, stop asking me about him.

467
00:30:51,480 --> 00:30:53,280
I'm telling you, we're really nothing!

468
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:55,760
Why would he take you home when you two are nothing?

469
00:30:55,760 --> 00:30:58,120
He obviously thinks there is something??

470
00:30:58,120 --> 00:31:00,160
Mom, don't you have any conscience?

471
00:31:00,160 --> 00:31:01,680
Your daughter's crazy.

472
00:31:01,680 --> 00:31:02,960
Who are you trying to marry her off to?

473
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:04,120
Crazy?

474
00:31:04,120 --> 00:31:05,000
Hey, Nam Eun-ki.

475
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:07,080
I hope you meet a girl who's exactly like me.

476
00:31:07,080 --> 00:31:08,040
Should I?

477
00:31:08,040 --> 00:31:09,800
Then I hope you meet a guy who's exactly like me, too.

478
00:31:09,800 --> 00:31:10,680
Are you crazy?

479
00:31:10,680 --> 00:31:11,600
Hey!

480
00:31:12,720 --> 00:31:15,840
Do you think I raised you kids

481
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:18,360
just to get a daughter-in-law and a son-in-law like you?

482
00:31:18,360 --> 00:31:20,120
If you're going to, just stay single all your life!

483
00:31:23,320 --> 00:31:24,240
Don't eat any more.

484
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:26,880
But I bought it.

485
00:31:26,880 --> 00:31:28,680
What's wrong with a daughter-in-law like me?

486
00:31:30,720 --> 00:31:32,040
Right, Dad?

487
00:31:32,760 --> 00:31:35,120
Dad, wouldn't you be happy with a son-in-law like me?

488
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:41,360
Ugh.

489
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:46,800
What's wrong with us? Aren't we fantastic?

490
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:48,280
Right?

491
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:49,040
Eat up.

492
00:31:49,040 --> 00:31:50,960
You eat up, too. You look a bit haggard today.

493
00:31:51,640 --> 00:31:52,440
Say ah.

494
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:03,880
Eun-ki.

495
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:08,360
What do you think of me?

496
00:32:10,320 --> 00:32:12,480
Let's say we're not childhood friends,

497
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:14,760
but that we just met for the first time today.

498
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:18,480
What do you think of me?

499
00:32:20,120 --> 00:32:22,360
- You're pretty. - Right?

500
00:32:22,360 --> 00:32:26,160
Then how would you feel if

501
00:32:26,160 --> 00:32:28,480
a girl like me said she liked you?

502
00:32:29,240 --> 00:32:30,440
It's a big thank you.

503
00:32:30,440 --> 00:32:32,040
Really?

504
00:32:32,040 --> 00:32:34,640
Yes. I'd date you right away.

505
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:35,640
You really would?

506
00:32:36,560 --> 00:32:38,120
Then I'd ask her.

507
00:32:38,120 --> 00:32:40,360
"You're into idols? At your age?

508
00:32:40,360 --> 00:32:43,240
You're not just any fan, but a homepage master? What's that?

509
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:44,720
You follow them around and take pictures?

510
00:32:44,720 --> 00:32:46,200
You've been doing that your entire life?

511
00:32:47,480 --> 00:32:49,360
Then does that mean I'm second to him?

512
00:32:49,360 --> 00:32:51,840
Choose: is it me or Cha Si-an?"

513
00:32:54,960 --> 00:32:56,280
Hey!

514
00:32:56,280 --> 00:32:57,800
You could've given me a more cookie-cutter answer.

515
00:32:57,800 --> 00:32:59,600
Why make it so realistic?

516
00:33:03,440 --> 00:33:04,360
Sung Duk-mi.

517
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:07,600
Date a guy to whom you can tell honestly

518
00:33:07,600 --> 00:33:10,200
and with confidence that you're a fan girl to the bone!

519
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:14,040
Not someone who you're worried will find out.

520
00:33:17,680 --> 00:33:21,040
Though I must admit, there aren't many guys like that out there.

521
00:33:35,240 --> 00:33:37,000
How much do you know about Duk-mi, anyway?

522
00:33:41,560 --> 00:33:43,960
See, she tells me everything.

523
00:33:43,960 --> 00:33:46,000
Without hiding anything.

524
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:48,280
But do you think she'll do the same with you?

525
00:33:59,040 --> 00:34:00,600
(The Road to Si-an)

526
00:34:01,600 --> 00:34:04,160
Hey, we even write back to each other on this site.

527
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:08,640
I can't believe my goal in this life is to be a water bottle.

528
00:34:08,640 --> 00:34:09,640
Water bottle?

529
00:34:10,480 --> 00:34:13,320
Lord, I have sinned.

530
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:15,320
Sinned? In what way?

531
00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:16,920
I'm sorry, Si-an!

532
00:34:18,840 --> 00:34:20,080
Sorry about what?

533
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:47,600
(Write a comment)

534
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:52,680
It seems there are two suns in this world.

535
00:34:55,960 --> 00:34:58,040
(It seems there are two suns in this world)

536
00:35:19,640 --> 00:35:21,920
(Si-an at the airport!)

537
00:35:22,880 --> 00:35:24,960
Date a guy to whom you can tell honestly

538
00:35:24,960 --> 00:35:27,560
and with confidence that you're a fan girl to the bone!

539
00:35:27,560 --> 00:35:31,160
Not someone who you're worried will find out.

540
00:35:33,640 --> 00:35:35,160
It's all because of this day.

541
00:35:36,240 --> 00:35:38,160
If it weren't for what happened this day,

542
00:35:38,160 --> 00:35:41,040
I wouldn't be feeling so guilty about deceiving him.

