00:56:07,000 --> 00:56:12,320
But the artwork itself cannot exist on its own.

812
00:56:12,320 --> 00:56:16,120
It only takes on value after it meets with an audience

813
00:56:16,120 --> 00:56:18,160
that sees it and feels something from it.

814
00:56:18,160 --> 00:56:20,040
That's why, as the director of Cheum,

815
00:56:20,040 --> 00:56:22,920
I want to change the prejudice that art is difficult and boring.

816
00:56:24,080 --> 00:56:27,560
Through an exhibition that is easy for anyone to approach.

817
00:56:27,560 --> 00:56:30,720
Oh, so the Celebrities' Collection will be that first step, huh?

818
00:56:31,840 --> 00:56:33,360
I'm looking forward to it.

819
00:56:33,360 --> 00:56:34,400
Thank you.

820
00:56:35,160 --> 00:56:36,720
No, thank you.

821
00:56:36,720 --> 00:56:41,000
Oh, and this is just out of my own curiosity.

822
00:56:41,000 --> 00:56:42,120
Once your term is up,

823
00:56:42,120 --> 00:56:44,800
will you be returning to New York?

824
00:56:44,800 --> 00:56:45,600
It's hard to say.

825
00:56:45,600 --> 00:56:49,160
Any chance you'll get married and settle in Korea?

826
00:56:49,160 --> 00:56:50,040
I'm sorry?

827
00:56:50,040 --> 00:56:52,960
I mean, if you started seeing someone in Korea,

828
00:56:52,960 --> 00:56:55,440
you could decide that you might like to settle here.

829
00:56:56,720 --> 00:56:58,120
I'll think about that.

830
00:56:58,120 --> 00:57:01,160
Saying you'll think about that??

831
00:57:01,160 --> 00:57:02,880
Does that mean you're seeing someone now?

832
00:57:15,680 --> 00:57:17,200
Hey, Young-sook.

833
00:57:17,200 --> 00:57:19,800
You better get yourself a new hanbok for Duk-mi's wedding.

834
00:57:19,800 --> 00:57:20,800
That's right!

835
00:57:22,160 --> 00:57:24,920
If it weren't for you, I would've been in trouble.

836
00:57:24,920 --> 00:57:25,920
So thank you.

837
00:57:27,360 --> 00:57:29,560
You know that I have other intentions, right?

838
00:57:31,080 --> 00:57:34,760
Here's the proposal for Mr. Cha's album and the exhibition.

839
00:57:34,760 --> 00:57:35,960
There's no need.

840
00:57:37,480 --> 00:57:39,080
Because I'm going to do it.

841
00:57:39,080 --> 00:57:40,440
Really?

842
00:57:40,440 --> 00:57:41,880
Thank you.

843
00:57:41,880 --> 00:57:43,000
Don't thank me,

844
00:57:43,000 --> 00:57:44,880
because I have other intentions, too.

845
00:57:47,720 --> 00:57:50,480
I'm doing this so I can work with Ryan, right next to him.

846
00:57:53,160 --> 00:57:55,080
I like Ryan, you see.

847
00:57:58,200 --> 00:58:00,720
You don't mind, do you?

848
00:58:00,720 --> 00:58:02,600
Because you're not really dating him anyway.

849
00:58:06,520 --> 00:58:08,200
How did you??

850
00:58:08,200 --> 00:58:09,320
I heard.

851
00:58:09,320 --> 00:58:12,520
That he's pretending to see you to help you out.

852
00:58:16,480 --> 00:58:17,920
But you know something?

853
00:58:18,600 --> 00:58:22,160
Ryan wants to end this fake relationship.

854
00:59:05,640 --> 00:59:08,520
